.TH "schedule_on_each_cpu" 9 "schedule_on_each_cpu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
schedule_on_each_cpu \- execute a function synchronously on each online CPU
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" schedule_on_each_cpu
.BI "(work_func_t func "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "func" 12
the function to call
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBschedule_on_each_cpu\fP executes \fIfunc\fP on each online CPU using the
system workqueue and blocks until all CPUs have completed.
\fBschedule_on_each_cpu\fP is very slow.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure.
